 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "2be84e11",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "(example_06_tri_prism_densities)="
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "b622aa14",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Triangle Prism Densities\n",
    "\n",
    "An example application of the `circle_bundles` pipeline to a dataset where the underlying model is a non-orientable 3-manifold which admits a circle bundle structure over $\\mathbb{RP}^{2}$ with non-trivial twisted Euler class. \n",
    "\n",
    "Also a demonstration of the bundle-coordinatization feature of `circle_bundles` which produces a topologically-faithful lower-dimensional representation of the data. \n",
    "\n",
    "We generate a dataset by applying random $SO(3)$ rotations to the vertices of a triangular prism embedded in the unit ball, then constructing 3D density functions on $\\overline{\\mathbb{B}}_{1}(0)$ from the rotated prisms which are Gaussian-distributed around their boundaries.  For analysis, we define an $\\mathbb{RP}^{2}$-valued feature map which roughly captures the axis of symmetry of each density. One can show that the underlying bundle structure is non-orientable with twisted Euler number $\\pm 3$.\n",
    "\n",
    "We recover the characteristic classes, which determines the topology of the total space up to homeomorphism (in particular, it is a quotient of $SO(3)$). We then restrict to a subset of the data which projects to an 'equator' $\\mathbb{RP}^{1}\\subset\\mathbb{RP}^{2}$ and verify that the restriction has the structure of a Klein bottle."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "id": "ef9902d1",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "\n",
    "import circle_bundles as cb"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "2d8b793b",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Start by generating a synthetic dataset of 3D densities represented as vectors of length $32^{3}$. Record the corresponding triangle meshes for visualization (represented as vectors in $\\mathbb{R}^{18}$):"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "id": "e4b8ba95",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "#Create the template triangle mesh\n",
    "mesh, face_groups = cb.make_tri_prism(height=1, radius=1)\n",
    "\n",
    "#Generate a random sample of SO(3) matrices\n",
    "n_samples = 5000\n",
    "rng = np.random.default_rng(0)\n",
    "so3_data = cb.sample_so3(n_samples, rng=rng)[0]\n",
    "\n",
    "#Apply rotations to the template mesh\n",
    "mesh_data = cb.get_mesh_sample(mesh, so3_data)\n",
    "\n",
    "#Generate 3D densities from the rotated meshes\n",
    "grid_size = 32  #density resolution\n",
    "sigma = 0.05  #density gaussian parameter\n",
    "\n",
    "data = cb.make_rotated_density_dataset(\n",
    "    mesh,\n",
    "    so3_data,\n",
    "    grid_size = grid_size,\n",
    "    sigma = sigma,\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "#Create visualization functions for triangle meshes and 3D densities\n",
    "vis_density = cb.make_density_visualizer(grid_size=grid_size)\n",
    "vis_mesh = cb.make_tri_prism_visualizer(mesh, face_groups)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "f93c9e29",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "View a small sample of the dataset, represented by 2D projections of the 3D densities and also by the triangle meshes used to produce the densities."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "id": "4ddabba1",

    "    max_samples=8, \n",

    "    sampling_method=\"first\", \n",
    "    pad_frac=0.3)\n",
    "plt.show()\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "c5a3d84d",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "$\\textbf{Note:}$ 2D projections of the 3D densities are computed by summing intensities along the z-axis, shown here as perpendicular to the screen.  In general, reflecting a rotated prism mesh through the z-axis may produce a very different 3D density, but the 2D projections will appear the same.  On the other hand, two prism meshes which differ by a rotation in the symmetry group of the prism yield indistinguishable 3D densities -- this is a genuine symmetry of the dataset.  \n",
    "\n",
    "For each 3D density, compute the principal component (up to sign in $\\mathbb{RP}^{2}$) associated with the smallest eigenvalue -- for densities in the dataset, this axis is always clearly defined and coincides with the axis of rotational symmetry. Record the $\\mathbb{RP}^{2}$ projections as unit vectors in the upper hemisphere of $\\mathbb{S}^{2}$:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "id": "1eb5cfae",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "base_points = cb.get_density_axes(data)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "49baeec8",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Construct a (good) open cover $\\mathcal{U} = \\{U_{j}\\}_{j=1}^{60}$ of $\\mathbb{RP}^{2}$ using a collection of nearly equidistant landmark points (see API reference section):"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "id": "28f8c484",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/markdown": [
       "### Cover And Nerve Summary\n",
       "- $n_\\text{sets} = 60$, $n_\\text{samples} = 5000$\n",
       "\n",
       "**Recorded Simplex Counts:**\n",
       "\n",
       "- $\\#(\\text{0-simplices}) = 60$\n",
       "- $\\#(\\text{1-simplices}) = 177$\n",
       "- $\\#(\\text{2-simplices}) = 118$\n",
       "- *No recorded simplices in dimensions* $\\ge 3$"
      ],
      "text/plain": [
       "<IPython.core.display.Markdown object>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"

   ],
   "source": [
    "n_landmarks = 60\n",
    "cover = cb.get_rp2_fibonacci_cover(base_points, n_pairs = n_landmarks)\n",
    "bundle = cb.Bundle(X = data, cover = cover, show_summary = True)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "e500d21d",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Observe that the Euler characteristic of $\\mathcal{U}$ is $\\chi = 60 - 177 + 118 = 1$, as expected for $\\mathbb{RP}^{2}$."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "fc30a1ac",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Compute a PCA projection for the data in each set $\\pi^{-1}(U_{j})$:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "id": "11131269",

    "plt.show()"
   ]

   "source": [
    "Show a PCA visualization of a 'fat fiber' of the projection map:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 11,
   "id": "ed943bf1",
   "metadata": {},

   "source": [
    "center_ind = 201\n",
    "r = 0.2\n",
    "dist_mat = cb.RP2UnitVectorMetric().pairwise(X=base_points)\n",
    "nearby_indices = np.where(dist_mat[center_ind] < r)[0]\n",
    "\n",
    "fiber_data = data[nearby_indices]\n",
    "vis_data = mesh_data[nearby_indices]\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "fig = plt.figure(figsize=(6, 3), dpi=120)\n",
    "ax1 = fig.add_subplot(1, 2, 1, projection=\"3d\")\n",
    "ax2 = fig.add_subplot(1, 2, 2, projection=\"3d\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# PCA labeled with density projections\n",
    "cb.fiber_vis(\n",
    "    fiber_data,\n",
    "    vis_func=vis_density,\n",
    "    max_images=200,\n",
    "    zoom=0.05,\n",
    "    ax=ax1,\n",
    "    show=False,\n",
    ")\n",
    "ax1.set_title(\"Fiber PCA\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Base visualization\n",
    "cb.base_vis(\n",
    "    base_points,\n",
    "    center_ind,\n",
    "    r,\n",
    "    dist_mat,\n",
    "    ax=ax2,\n",
    "    show=False,\n",
    ")\n",
    "ax2.set_title(\"Base Projections\")\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()\n"
   ]
  },

   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "7ddde93a",

    "Construct local circular coordinates using $\\text{PCA}_{2}$, then compute approximate transition matrices and characteristic clases:"
   ]
  },

       "$\\displaystyle \\begin{array}{lrrrrr}\\textbf{Stage} & k & r & |W_r^{(1)}| & |W_r^{(2)}| & |W_r^{(3)}| \\\\ \\hline \\text{Full nerve} & 0 & 0.251 & 177 & 118 & 0 \\\\ \\text{w cobirth} & 0 & \\infty & 177 & 118 & 0 \\\\ \\text{w codeath} & 114 & 0.099 & 63 & 11 & 0 \\\\ \\text{Euler cobirth} & 0 & \\infty & 177 & 118 & 0 \\\\ \\text{Euler codeath} & 1 & 0.251 & 176 & 116 & 0\\end{array}$"
      ],

   ],
   "source": [
    "triv_result = bundle.get_local_trivs()\n",
    "class_result = bundle.get_classes(show_classes = True, show_persistence = True)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "a7f3c55a",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Observe that the twisted Euler class becomes trivial as soon as a single edge is removed.  This is to be expected, since the resulting subcomplex deformation retracts onto its 1-skeleton.  On the other hand, the orientation class does not become trivial until many edges are removed. This is also reasonable, since one can show that the restriction of a non-orientable bundle over $\\mathbb{RP}^{2}$ to an 'equator' $\\mathbb{RP}^{1}$ is still non-orientable (hence non-trivial) -- see below. In any case, the weight of even the heaviest edge is relatively small, suggesting that our model is likely reliable across the entire nerve. "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "daf9bc38",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Show a visualization of the 1-skeleton of the nerve of $\\mathcal{U}$.  For readability, each open set is represented by a node with the triangle mesh underlying a representative density. Edges are colored according to the computed orientation class representative (blue for 1 and red for -1):"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 15,
   "id": "d70a8e36",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {

     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"

   ],
   "source": [
    "dist_mat = cb.RP2UnitVectorMetric().pairwise(X = cover.landmarks, Y = base_points)\n",
    "inds = np.argmin(dist_mat, axis = 1)\n",
    "node_data = mesh_data[inds]\n",
    "\n",
    "vertex_coords = cover.landmarks[:,:2]\n",
    "node_labels = [f\"{i+1}\" for i in range(vertex_coords.shape[0])]\n",
    "\n",
    "verts = list(range(bundle.n_sets))\n",
    "\n",
    "edges = bundle.get_simplices(dims=1)\n",
    "\n",
    "fig, axes = cb.nerve_vis(\n",
    "    cover.landmarks[:, :2],\n",
    "    vertices=verts,\n",
    "    edges=edges,\n",
    "    cochains={1: class_result.reps.sw1_O1},\n",
    "    base_colors={0: 'black', 1: 'black', 2: 'pink'},\n",
    "    cochain_cmaps={1: {1: 'blue', -1: 'darkred'}},\n",
    "    opacity=0,\n",
    "    node_size=17,\n",
    "    line_width=1,\n",
    "    node_labels=None,\n",
    "    fontsize=8,\n",
    "    font_color='white',\n",
    "    vis_func=vis_mesh,\n",
    "    data=node_data,\n",
    "    image_zoom=0.05,\n",
    "    title='1-Skeleton Of The Nerve',\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "04e0c11a",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Now, to construct a lower-dimensional representation of the high-dimensional dataset, compute a classifying map to $Gr(2)$ representing the underlying circle bundle and compute the pullback of the canonical circle bundle $V(2)\\times_{O(2)}\\mathbb{S}^{1}$ (see theory section for details):  "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 20,
   "id": "8e02ad24-8947-4790-b9b3-0c554150782c",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Ambient output dimension: 24\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "bundle_map_results = bundle.get_bundle_map(packing = 'coloring2')\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f'Ambient output dimension: {bundle_map_results.F.shape[1]}')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "ca6dbcff-fdf6-476a-994e-ae5ea65e882f",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Notice that the pullback data lives in the ambient space $\\mathbb{R}^{24}$ (whereas the original dataset lives in $\\mathbb{R}^{32768}$). \n",
    "\n",
    "Now, consider the data which projects to the 'equator' $\\mathbb{RP}^{1}\\subset \\mathbb{RP}^{2}$:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 76,
   "id": "f7a03471",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Equator band: 686 / 5000 samples (eps=0.15).\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "eps = 0.15  # thickness of equatorial band (in the chosen RP^2 embedding/coords)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Points near the equator: last coordinate close to 0\n",
    "eq_mask = np.abs(base_points[:, -1]) < eps\n",
    "print(f\"Equator band: {np.sum(eq_mask)} / {bundle.X.shape[0]} samples (eps={eps}).\")\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "# Parametrize the equator by an angle in RP^1 (theta ~ theta + pi)\n",
    "eq_base_points = base_points[eq_mask,:2]\n",
    "eq_base_angles = np.arctan2(eq_base_points[:,1], eq_base_points[:, 0]) % np.pi\n",
    "\n",
    "#Construct the total space\n",
    "eq_data = np.concatenate([np.array([np.cos(2*eq_base_angles), np.sin(2*eq_base_angles)]).T, \n",
    "                             bundle_map_results.F[eq_mask]],axis = 1)\n",
    "\n",
    "eq_mesh_data = mesh_data[eq_mask]"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 85,
   "id": "31b2a9c8-6434-45c9-ab52-0a962385f8f4",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/latex": [
       "$\\displaystyle \\begin{aligned}\\textbf{Characteristic Classes} & \\\\[8pt]\\quad \\text{Stiefel--Whitney} &:\\quad w_1 \\neq 0\\ (\\text{non-orientable})\\\\[4pt]\\quad \\text{(twisted) Euler} &:\\quad \\tilde{e}=0\\end{aligned}$"
      ],
      "text/plain": [
       "<IPython.core.display.Math object>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "n_landmarks = 8\n",
    "lmk_angs = np.linspace(0, np.pi, n_landmarks, endpoint=False)\n",
    "landmarks = np.array([np.cos(lmk_angs), np.sin(lmk_angs)]).T\n",
    "overlap = 1.2\n",
    "radius = overlap * np.pi / (2*n_landmarks)\n",
    "\n",
    "eq_cover = cb.get_metric_ball_cover(\n",
    "    np.array([np.cos(eq_base_angles), np.sin(eq_base_angles)]).T, \n",
    "    landmarks, \n",
    "    radius = radius, \n",
    "    metric = cb.RP1UnitVectorMetric()\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "eq_bundle = cb.Bundle(X = eq_data, cover = eq_cover)\n",
    "eq_local_triv_result = eq_bundle.get_local_trivs()\n",
    "eq_class_result = eq_bundle.get_classes(show_classes = True)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "40af97c2",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The characteristic classes confirm that the restricted pullback dataset has the topology of a Klein bottle embedded in $\\mathbb{R}^{26}$.\n",
    "\n",
    "Compute a global 'coordinate system' for the restricted dataset after dropping the heaviest edge from the nerve of the cover of $\\mathbb{RP}^{1}$, then show a visualization of the coordinatized densities, represented by both the corresponding triangle meshes and 2D projections of the densities themselves:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 84,

    "eq_fiber_angles = eq_bundle.get_global_trivialization()\n",
    "\n",
    "coords = np.column_stack([eq_base_angles, eq_fiber_angles])\n",
    "\n",
    "fig, (ax1, ax2) = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(22, 10), dpi=200)\n",

    "plt.show()\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "2ff6ea8b",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Notice that base projection roughly corresponds to axis of symmetry, as expected.  Upon carefuly inspection, one can see that coordinatized densities in each column approximately traverse a 1/3 rotation about the axis of symmetry, though the direction of rotation abruptly changes between columns 1 and 2 (roughly where the cut was made). The top and bottom rows of the diagram also roughly coincide, as do the first and last columns. "
   ]
  }
